After the planes hit, voting was halted and rescheduled for two weeks later.
A pandemic, with its invisible enemy, presents a more miasmic challenge to voting, though.
It is highly unusual to introduce a new way of voting during a general election; election officials will need time and training to adapt, and they may not have either.
And voting by mail is a less than optimal solution for voters without a fixed address or those who live on tribal lands.
Hasen pointed out that Republican voters, who skew older, may prefer voting at home.